Question: Do you think it is ok for the government to read your emails for counter-terrorism purposes?
Answer:
I think the government should not read personal emails in any case, even for the purpose of counter-terrorism.
First, pesonal email is the property of one individual, who deserve respection. And such respection should be maintained in any case in a modern country.
Besides, abuse of such unfair right could lead to some serious consequences even though its initial purpose is good.